/-
This module formalizes the "d=2 miracle" and related properties for the interleaved quartic invariant of matrices. It proves that for 2x2 matrices, the trace of S₁S₂S₁S₂ reduces to degree-2 invariants (trace and determinant), specifically tr(S₁S₂S₁S₂) = tr(S₁S₂)² - 2·det(S₁)·det(S₂). It also verifies the commutative reduction, provides explicit 3x3 counterexamples showing this reduction fails at d=3, and establishes the stratification of invariants at d=2.
-/

